title: The Lady in the Bottle
description: American astronaut Tony Nelson splashes down near a deserted island and finds a bottle that contains a beautiful genie named Jeannie. After helping him get rescued he sets her free, but she prefers to come home with him. Besides she is very much in love with her handsome master and she will grant his every wish or desire no matter how much trouble he gets in.

title: My Hero?
description: Jeannie blinks Tony to ancient Persia to defend her honor while Jeannie announces to her parents that this is the man she plans to marry.

title: Guess What Happened on the Way to the Moon?
description: On a survival mission Jeannie gives him every possible comfort.

title: Jeannie and the Marriage Caper
description: When Tony's future father-in-law is accepting an ambassadorship, he offers Tony a prestigious position if he leaves the Air Force.

title: G.I. Jeannie
description: When Jeannie says she wants to be his secretary, Tony tells Jeannie that she has to join the Air Force.

title: The Yacht Murder Case
description: After Tony argues with Jeannie on a yacht and she blinks home, two witnesses think that he pushed her overboard and murdered her.

title: Anybody Here Seen Jeannie?
description: Jeannie sabotages Tony's tests prior to his launch because she doesn't want him breaking his tether on a spacewalk and being lost in space.

title: The Americanization of Jeannie
description: After reading an article in a magazine, Jeannie tries to become the typical American woman.

title: The Moving Finger
description: When Jeannie becomes jealous of Tony dating a movie star, she tries to become one but finds out that genies cannot be photographed.

title: Djinn and Water
description: Jeannie brings her great-grandfather to Cocoa Beach to teach Tony how to desalinate water.

title: Whatever Became of Baby Custer?
description: A neighborhood boy sees Jeannie performing her magic and tells Doctor Bellows.

title: Where'd You Go-Go?
description: Jeannie goes out with Roger to make Tony jealous. Roger falls for Jeannie thinking that she is a normal woman.

title: Russian Roulette
description: When Tony and Roger are entertaining two Russian cosmonauts, Roger inadvertently gives the female Russian Jeannie's bottle with Jeannie in it.

title: What House Across the Street?
description: Jeannie invites Roger Healey to visit her home that she blinks one onto a nearby vacant lot and creates parents based upon characters she sees on TV.

title: Too Many Tonys
description: Jeannie creates a second Tony that adores her the way she wishes her master would.

title: Get Me to Mecca on Time
description: On the day of Ramdah masters must journey to Mecca to recite the ancient words or their genie will lose her powers and disappear.

title: Richest Astronaut in the World
description: Roger finally discovers that Jeannie is a genie and steals her bottle. After making him extremely wealthy, NASA has him arrested on suspicious of selling government secrets to foreign countries.

title: Is There an Extra Jeannie in the House?
description: Roger thinks that two stage magicians are his own two genies.

title: Never Try to Outsmart a Jeannie
description: Tony says that Jeannie can come to Europe with him if she travels as a normal woman and can get a passport.

title: My Master, the Doctor
description: When Tony mentions that he always dreamed of being a surgeon Jeannie blinks him into the operating room where Tony gets accused of impersonating a doctor.

title: Jeannie and the Kidnap Caper
description: Tired of Jeannie using her magic around the house he asks Jeannie to promise to not use her magic for him again. Next thing he knows is that he is captured by Red Chinese spies and all Jeannie can do is watch.

title: How Lucky Can You Get?
description: Unbeknownst to Tony, greedy Roger brings Jeannie with them to Reno and gets in trouble at the gambling tables.

title: Watch the Birdie
description: Tony becomes General Peterson's golf partner when Jeannie makes him play like Arnold Palmer.

title: Permanent House Guest
description: After Doctor Bellows can not prove that Major Nelson had an elephant in his house, he moves in to catch him in the act.

title: Bigger Than a Bread Box and Better Than a Genie
description: Tony investigates a phony fortune teller who is almost proved real with Jeannie's help.

title: My Master, the Great Rembrandt
description: Trouble starts when Jeannie replaces Tony's copy of a Rembrandt with the original painting.

title: My Master, the Thief
description: Jeannie steals a pair of slippers from a museum that were hers 2000 years ago.

title: This Is Murder
description: When Tony has to escort a princess around, Jeannie announces that due to a family feud she has to kill her. To save the princess Tony sends Jeannie around the world with tasks so massive that she will miss the three days of her visit.

title: My Master, the Magician
description: When Doctor Bellows finds Tony floating in midair, he insists that he perform that same trick at the NASA talent show.

title: I'll Never Forget What's Her Name
description: Tony hits his head, forgets who Jeannie is and asks her to marry him despite Roger's objections.

title: Happy Anniversary
description: To celebrate their first anniversary, Jeannie makes Tony splashdown on the same desert island he originally found her on. Tony finds another genie who trapped Jeannie in her bottle 2000 years ago.

title: Always on Sunday
description: When Jeannie thinks that her master needs more time to rest she makes everyday Sunday.

title: My Master, the Rich Tycoon
description: When Jeannie lets in a man who scoffs at her master's taste, she makes several valuable works of art appear. Afterwards the man introduces himself as from the IRS.

title: My Master, the Rainmaker
description: Through Jeannie's misguided attempts to help, Doctor Bellows thinks that Tony can make it rain at will.

title: My Wild-Eyed Master
description: When Tony says that astronauts should have perfect vision, Jeannie blinks and first gives him X-ray vision followed by making him almost blind.

title: What's New, Poodle Dog?
description: When Roger will not tell Jeannie about their two dates, Jeannie turns Roger into a poodle that ends up in the dog pound.

title: Fastest Gun in the East
description: Jeannie sends Tony back to the old West when he wishes he could have lived back then.

title: How to Be a Genie in 10 Easy Lessons
description: Roger convinces that "The Tales of the Arabian Nights" would be a good manual on how a genie should act to his master. Tony tells Jeannie to read it, but Roger didn't let him know that it was about stories of genies who torture their masters.

title: Who Needs a Green-Eyed Jeannie?
description: Jeannie is jealous of Tony meeting an old flame. When he gets her to promise to not interfere again, the old flame turns out to be the wife of a mobster that is now after Tony.

title: The Girl Who Never Had a Birthday: Part 1
description: Jeannie is so sad that she doesn't know her birthday that she starts to vanish feet first.

title: The Girl Who Never Had a Birthday: Part 2
description: Tony runs around trying to get Jeannie's birthday from Roger who had been sent to Alaska.

title: How Do You Beat Superman?
description: Jeannie blinks up an attentive suitor named Tony Millionaire to make Tony Nelson jealous.

title: My Master, the Great Caruso
description: When General Peterson catches Tony singing with Enrico Caruso's voice he enters him in the NASA talent contest. Unfortunately Jeannie promised to never give him that voice again.

title: The World's Greatest Lover
description: Feeling sorry for Roger Jeannie makes all women who see him fall madly in love with him including the girlfriend of a mobster.

title: Jeannie Breaks the Bank
description: Jeannie gets Tony in trouble by putting $3 million in his Christmas club account.

title: My Master, the Author
description: Jeannie writes a book on childcare using Tony's name that becomes a best seller. Now he has to babysit Doctor Bellow's and General Perterson's niece and nephew.

title: The Greatest Invention in the World
description: When Roger wishes that he hadn't spilled coffee on Tony's jacket, his jacket becomes impervious to tears, stains, cutting or burning. Dr. Bellows witnesses these miracles and has to prove it.

title: My Master, the Spy
description: Tony is suspected of being a spy when he is at a NASA meeting and seen in Paris having lunch with Jeannie at the same time.

title: You Can't Arrest Me, I Don't Have a Driver's License
description: Jeannie drives off with Tony's car and Tony ends up in traffic court.

title: One of Our Bottles Is Missing
description: After Mrs. Bellows has Jeannie's bottle copied, she takes home the real one.

title: My Master, the Civilian
description: After Tony accepts job in the private sector, Tony and Jeannie check up on his future and find it very successful. Fooling Tony into thinking things will be horrible, he still takes the job because he feels that the aerospace industry needs him.

title: There Goes the Best Genie I Ever Had
description: When Tony learns that he can send back his genie on Haji's birthday he contemplates whether to keep the trouble causing Jeannie or not.

title: The Greatest Entertainer in the World
description: After Tony can't get Sammy Davis Junior for General Peterson's birthday party, Jeannie helps him out by duplicating Sammy so he can be in both places.

title: My Incredible Shrinking Master
description: Jeannie accidentally shrinks Tony and he gets attacked by a cat just as Jeannie's dream prophesied.

title: My Master, the Pirate
description: Tony is sent back to deal with Captain Kidd to prove his bravery.

title: A Secretary Is Not a Toy
description: Jeannie becomes General Peterson's secretary and then becomes accused of being a spy since she can not pass the security investigation. Jeannie only wanted Peterson to make him a general.

title: There Goes the Bride
description: Jeannie puts a love spell on Tony which displeases Haji, the Master of all Genies. Haji makes Tony have several accidents that can only be undone if the love spell is taken off of him.

title: My Master, Napoleon's Buddy
description: Upon Tony's request, Jeannie sends him back in time to talk to Napoleon who wants to execute him as a spy.

title: The Birds and the Bees Bit
description: Learning that genies lose their powers if they marry a mortal, Tony proposes to Jeannie. After Roger and Jeannie learn that their children might get magical powers, Jeannie keeps Roger away so that Tony won't learn that little fact.

title: My Master, the Swinging Bachelor
description: Jeannie mistakes the pretty caterer as the reason for a dinner party she was left out if. The guests enjoy a cake that reverts them to childhood.

title: The Mod Party
description: Tony and Roger makes up excuses to get out of a meeting with Dr. Bellows to attend a Mod Party. Things are fine until Dr. Bellows shows up at Tony's house.

title: Fly Me to the Moon
description: Jeannie turns a NASA chimp into a human.

title: Jeannie or the Tiger
description: Jeannie's sister shows up for the first time trapping her sister in her bottle and plotting to steal her master.

title: The Second Greatest Con Artist in the World
description: A con artist convinces Jeannie that a Hawaiian beach is covered in diamonds.

title: My Turned-On Master
description: Jeannie gives Tony her powers for 24 hours.

title: My Master, the Weakling
description: During a physical fitness course, Jeannie gives the tough Navy trainer the personality of his sweet aunt.

title: Jeannie, the Hip Hippie
description: Jeannie blinks up a music group when Dr. Bellow's wife assigns the job to Tony Nelson.

title: Everybody's a Movie Star
description: A movie is being made at the Space Center with Tony and Roger and Jeannie gets involved.

title: Who Are You Calling a Genie?
description: Jeannie loses her memory while at NASA and Tony has to rescue her from the authorities.

title: Meet My Master's Mother
description: Tony's mother comes to visit and she is determined to marry him off much to Jeannie's annoyance.

title: Here Comes Bootsie Nightingale
description: How does one hide from Jeannie that fact that Tony has to escort a beautiful movie star?

title: Tony's Wife
description: Jeannie's sister tells her that she was born under the sign of the jinx and that she has to leave Tony for 15 years. Jeannie tries to find Tony another woman.

title: Jeannie and the Great Bank Robbery
description: Tony tells Jeannie to go help someone else and she unknowingly helps some crooks rob a bank.

title: My Son, the Genie
description: Jeannie has to mentor an inept new genie just when the President of the United States is coming to visit Tony.

title: Jeannie Goes to Honolulu
description: Jeannie follows Tony to Hawaii and finds him seeing the Admiral's daughter.

title: Battle of Waikiki
description: While in Hawaii, Jeannie brings back King Kamehameha who feels that his people have forgotten him.

title: Genie, Genie, Who's Got the Genie?: Part 1
description: Jeannie gets trapped in a NASA safe that is being sent to the moon.

title: Genie, Genie, Who's Got the Genie?: Part 2
description: Jeannie gets trapped in a NASA safe that is being sent to the moon.

title: Genie, Genie, Who's Got the Genie?: Part 3
description: Jeannie gets trapped in a NASA safe that is being sent to the moon.

title: Genie, Genie, Who's Got the Genie?: Part 4
description: Jeannie gets trapped in a NASA safe that is being sent to the moon.

title: Please, Don't Feed the Astronauts
description: After an experiment in nutrition, a Navy Commander sends Tony and Roger out on a survival mission. Jeannie does her usual in trying to help.

title: My Master, the Ghostbreaker
description: Tony inherits a haunted English mansion.

title: Divorce, Genie Style
description: Mrs. Bellows finds Jeannie in her harem costume thinking that Tony is her tyrannical husband. To Mrs. Bellows Jeannie needs a divorce.

title: My Double-Crossing Master
description: Jeannie falls for Tony's British alter ego after he makes a bet with Roger.

title: Have You Ever Had a Genie Hate You?
description: Due to Jeannie's sister's meddling, Jeannie now hates Tony.

title: Operation: First Couple on the Moon
description: Jeannie's sister gets assigned to Tony on the first couple on the moon project.

title: Haven't I Seen Me Someplace Before?
description: Roger gets a wish for his birthday and switches places with Tony before an important mission.

title: U.F.Oh Jeannie
description: Landing in a flying saucer spacecraft, Tony and Roger are captured by hillbillies who think that they are martians.

title: Jeannie and the Wild Pipchicks
description: Magical candy is taken to NASA and it brings out the inner desires of anyone who eats it.

title: Tomorrow Is Not Another Day
description: Jeannie blinks up tomorrow's newspaper and the headline reads that an unknown astronaut breaks his leg. Now who needs saving?

title: Abdullah
description: Jeannie is babysitting her nephew Abdullah and Tony is the only one who can stop the infant from crying.

title: The Used Car Salesman
description: Instead of taking Tony's car to a repair shop, it ends up on a used car lot.

title: Djinn, Djinn, Go Home
description: While picking up items for her charity auction at Major Nelson's house, Amanda Bellows finds a friendly little stray dog and decides to adopt it. Later on, the dogs turns invisible and terrorizes half of NASA, convincing Major Nelson that it is Jeannie's long lost dog, Djinn Djinn.

title: The Strongest Man in the World
description: Due to Jeannie's meddling, Tony ends up in a boxing match.

title: Indispensable Jeannie
description: When Jeannie is sent away during a compatibility test for Tony and Roger, Jeannie puts the house on automatic granting their every wish.

title: Jeannie and the Top Secret
description: Tony gets into trouble with Jeannie when he's ordered to deliver a top secret film to the Pentagon on his and Jeannie's third anniversary together.

title: How to Marry an Astronaut
description: Jeannie II returns and says that she can finally help her sister get Tony to marry her. She shows her how easy it is to get a man to fall in love without the aid of magic. To this end Jeannie II uses Roger as her guinea pig. Eventually she gets Roger to propose, and when Jeannie tries to use the same technique on Tony she fails miserably. However, it turns out that this is just another scheme by Jeannie II to finally get Tony into her clutches.

title: Dr. Bellows Goes Sane
description: Doctor Bellows assembles a complete dossier on Tony to prove his case against Tony for General Peterson.

title: Jeannie, My Guru
description: Tony must hide the boyfriend of General Schafer's daughter since the General hates hippies.

title: The Case of My Vanishing Master: Part 1
description: The real Tony shows up in time to stop the wedding and then is tortured by Jeannie thinking that he is the phony Tony.

title: The Case of My Vanishing Master: Part 2
description: Roger accidentally finds out that Tony has been replaced by a double and races to Tony's house to prevent the double from not only marrying Jeannie, but to prevent Doctor Bellows from finding out about her. They are successful on both fronts, but still have no clue as to where the real Tony is. However, it is revealed that the impostor Tony is also a double agent working for a foreign power sent to steal the project the real Tony was working for. Things really get complicated when the real Tony returns home.

title: Ride 'Em Astronaut
description: After being the millionth customer at a local market, Jeannie become queen of a local rodeo that Tony has to enter.

title: Invisible House for Sale
description: People start visiting the house after Jeannie puts up a 'for sale' sign because she wants Tony to spend more time with her. Tony says that he doesn't want anyone else to see that house so she makes it invisible.

title: Jeannie, the Governor's Wife
description: Jeannie decides that Tony should run for governor even though he is in the military and he would get thrown out of NASA.

title: Is There a Doctor in the House?
description: Jeannie's mother puts a spell on Tony that he fall asleep whenever someone whistles. Jeannie tries to get the spell reversed, but Dr Bellows accidentally gets the same spell.

title: The Biggest Star in Hollywood
description: Jeannie gets a guest shot on "Laugh-In."

title: The Case of the Porcelain Puppy
description: When Jeannie learns a new spell to turn things to porcelain, Jeannie accidentally turns her dog Djinn-Djinn to porcelain.

title: Jeannie for the Defense
description: Tony gets caught in a speed trap and then becomes victim of a hit-and-run scam in a small town where Roger and he go fishing. Jeannie comes to the rescue.

title: Nobody Loves a Fat Astronaut
description: Jeannie's sister makes NASA throw Tony out of the space program by making them think he is unfit physically and mentally.

title: Around the World in 80 Blinks
description: Jeannie tries to return Tony from a spaceflight to treat his cold and brings down the wrong astronaut.

title: Jeannie-Go-Round
description: Jeannie's sister causes havoc at a nightclub in front of the Bellows when Jeannie is locked in her bottle.

title: Jeannie and the Secret Weapon
description: When Tony and Roger are trying to make a spacecraft fly, Jeannie does it with one blink. Tony tells her to get rid of it so she gives it to a boy in the park that has an inventor father. Tony gets accused of selling government secrets.

title: Blackmail Order Bride
description: Tony is blackmailed when a phony wife and children show up at his home.

title: Jeannie at the Piano
description: After Jeannie places a hex on a NASA piano so that the player sounds like an expert, Tony feels that only he can play it and ends up on a concert tour.

title: Djinn Djinn, the Pied Piper
description: Djinn Djinn the uniform hating dog returns recking havoc with General Schaffer's dog.

title: Guess Who's Going to Be a Bride?: Part 1
description: After another rebuff by Tony to marry her, Jeannie takes up her uncle's offer to become queen of a foreign country.

title: Guess Who's Going to Be a Bride?: Part 2
description: After Jeannie leaves, Tony realizes he can't live without her and goes after Jeannie. When they return to NASA. Tony's announcement that they are engaged is a surprise even to Jeannie.

title: Jeannie's Beauty Cream
description: Jeannie gives Amanda Bellows some of her beauty cream that turns her into the most beautiful woman at NASA, but no one recognizes her.

title: Jeannie and the Bachelor Party
description: A bachelor party thrown for Tony must be kept secret from Amada Bellows and the other NASA wives.

title: The Blood of Jeannie
description: Jeannie must find a substitute for her marriage license blood test since genies have green blood.

title: See You in C-U-B-A
description: After blinking Tony away from a mission, she returns him to his plane which she lands in Cuba instead of Puerto Rico.

title: The Mad Home Wrecker
description: The Bellows want to have the Nelson house redecorated for a wedding present, however the decorator they chose wants to turn the house into a nightmare.

title: Uncle a Go-Go
description: Two of Jeannie's English uncles show up to approve Tony prior to their marriage.

title: The Wedding
description: Tony and Jeannie finally get married at a big public wedding though unfortunately genies don't photograph.

title: My Sister, the Home Wrecker
description: Jeannie's sister shows up and makes Tony and Jeannie's friends think that she is having an affair.

title: Jeannie, the Matchmaker
description: Both Tony and Jeannie are trying to play matchmaker with single Roger.

title: Never Put a Genie on a Budget
description: New housewife Jeannie goes overboard when Tony puts her on a budget.

title: Please Don't Give My Jeannie No More Wine
description: At a dinner party a wine is mistakenly served that makes people invisible.

title: One of Our Hotels Is Growing
description: When their hotel is filled up, Jeannie blinks on a thirteenth floor and they must spend their entire vacation waiting on the Bellows so they won't find out.

title: The Solid Gold Jeannie
description: An overzealous Jeannie blinks herself into Tony's isolation unit after he returns from moon and must stay. She turns herself into a solid gold statue to not appear conspicuous, but can she stay that way?

title: Mrs. Djinn Djinn
description: Due to a silly misunderstanding, Roger tells everyone that Jeannie is expecting a child. But, it is actually Jeannie's dog, Mrs. Djinn Djinn who is about to deliver puppies.

title: Jeannie and the Curious Kid
description: A nephew of the Bellows stays with the Nelsons and learns Jeannie's secret.

title: Jeannie, the Recording Secretary
description: To win a best husband contest, Jeannie blinks Tony back from his training in a very sleepy state.

title: Help, Help, a Shark
description: When Tony causes General Schafer to lose a pool match, Tony finds that he must win with Jeannie's help, of course.

title: Eternally Yours, Jeannie
description: Jeannie gets jealous when Tony receives a note from a former girlfriend who is visiting.

title: An Astronaut in Sheep's Clothing
description: For their six month anniversary, Jeannie wants to knit Tony a sweater.

title: Hurricane Jeannie
description: A hurricane traps Tony, Jeannie, Roger and Dr. Bellows overnight in the Nelson's house. Tony has a frightening dream that Dr. Bellows finally learns the truth about Jeannie's magic powers.

title: One Jeannie Beats Four of a Kind
description: There is a card shark working NASA over.

title: My Master, the Chili King
description: Jeannie and Tony's cousin want to make Tony the chili king even though NASA forbids its astronauts to make commercial endorsements.
